                        </svg>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="pipe-body">
                    <p class="pipe-name">Request::fromGlobals()</p>
                    <p class="pipe-desc">PHP superglobals captured into a typed, immutable Request object. Method, URI, headers, body — all normalised.</p>
                    <span class="pipe-code">luany/core</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pipe-step" role="listitem">
                <div class="pipe-icon-col">
                    <div class="pipe-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="pipe-body">
                    <p class="pipe-name">Global Middleware Pipeline</p>
                    <p class="pipe-desc">Every request passes through global middleware before routing. Short-circuit at any point. CSRF, auth, rate limiting — all here.</p>
                    <span class="pipe-code">Kernel::$middleware</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pipe-step" role="listitem">
                <div class="pipe-icon-col">
                    <div class="pipe-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/>
                            <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="pipe-body">
                    <p class="pipe-name">Route::handle()</p>
                    <p class="pipe-desc">Router matches method + URI. Named routes, route groups, resource routes, per-route middleware pipeline — all resolved here.</p>
                    <span class="pipe-code">luany/core · Router</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pipe-step" role="listitem">
                <div class="pipe-icon-col">
                    <div class="pipe-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M9 21V9"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="pipe-body">
                    <p class="pipe-name">Controller → LTE Engine</p>
                    <p class="pipe-desc">Controller returns a value. LTE compiles the view via AST, caches compiled PHP. Auto-reload in debug mode, persistent cache in production.</p>
                    <span class="pipe-code">luany/lte · Engine</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pipe-step" role="listitem">
                <div class="pipe-icon-col">
                    <div class="pipe-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <polyline points="22 8 22 16 16 20 8 20 2 16 2 8 8 4 16 4 22 8"/>
                            <polyline points="22 8 16 12 16 20"/><polyline points="2 8 8 12 8 20"/>
                            <line x1="8" y1="12" x2="16" y2="12"/>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="pipe-body">
                    <p class="pipe-name">Response::send()</p>
                    <p class="pipe-desc">Typed Response with status code, headers, and body. Send flushes to the client. Kernel::terminate() runs post-send cleanup.</p>
                    <span class="pipe-code">luany/core · Response</span>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>

